T1  - Editorial Comment: The Academy and Ecumenism
AU  - Vance, Stanley Editor
Y1  - 1967/12/01
PY  - 1967
DA  - 1967/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amj.1967.19207092
DO  - 10.5465/amj.1967.19207092
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 326
EP  - 328
VL  - 10
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The author comments on how ecumenical trends in business affect the area of management theory. The author discusses the ecumenical trends he witnessed at the International Meetings of The Institute of Management Sciences (TIMS) on August 20-25, 1967, such as noticing the international character of the meetings and the wide subject areas of study of the attending colleges. The author discusses the admission standards of the Academy of Management, and warns that if the Academy moves in the ecumenical direction and includes more members in its scope, the organization must be prepared for the influx of people and subject matters at its meetings.
AB  - The author comments on how ecumenical trends in business affect the area of management theory. The author discusses the ecumenical trends he witnessed at the International Meetings of The Institute of Management Sciences (TIMS) on August 20-25, 1967, such as noticing the international character of the meetings and the wide subject areas of study of the attending colleges. The author discusses the admission standards of the Academy of Management, and warns that if the Academy moves in the ecumenical direction and includes more members in its scope, the organization must be prepared for the influx of people and subject matters at its meetings.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amj.1967.19207092
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amj.1967.19207092
